<FIRST>u i PM-BRF--ChildPlummets     03-20 0152</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Child Plummets,0154</SECOND>
<HEAD>Boy Survives 15-Floor Drop</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 2-year-old boy plunged 15 floors
down a rubbish chute inside a Penang city apartment building but
suffered only bruises when he landed on a pile of garbage, a
newspaper reported today.
   The daily New Straits Times said that Firdaus Zainal Abidin was
playing other children Monday when the youngster's sister told their
father the boy was missing.
   The boy's father, Army Cpl. Zainal Abidin Saad, said he looked
everywhere for the boy before noticing the rubbish chute was open,
the newspaper reported.
   Zainal rushed down to the ground floor and found his son face
down and crying on top of the rubbish, the newspaper said.
   He rushed his son to the hospital, where doctors examined him and
sent him home, saying he had no injury other than bruises on his
forehead and elbow, the New Straits Times said.
</TEXT>
