<FIRST>r a AM-OilFires 3rdLd-Writethru a0408 03-20 0202</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Oil Fires, 3rd Ld - Writethru, a0408,0201</SECOND>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADs with three grafs to UPDATE with at least 13 injured; picks
up 4th graf pvs; DELETES final graf.</HEAD>
<HEAD>Two Offshore Rigs Catch Fire; 13 Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fires and explosions hit two off-shore
oil-producing platforms Sunday night, injuring at least 13 workers
and forcing the evacuations of 25 to 30, the Coast Guard said.
   There were no immediate reports of fatalities, said Lt. Bob
Carson, a Coast Guard spokesman at New Orleans.
   At least 13 crewmembers from one of the two rigs were injured,
said Coast Guard Cmdr. Gerry Donohoe, pilot of one of the
helicopters that evacuated some of the injured to a New Orleans area
hospital. The injuries included second- or third-degree burns, he
said.
   Coast Guard and civilian helicopters joined in evacuating the
crewmen, Carson said.
   Firefighters extinguished the blaze on one rig late Sunday but
were still battling the fire on the second platform, authorities
said. The two rigs are connected by a catwalk.
   Both rigs are operated by Atlantic Richfield Co. in the Gulf of
Mexico four miles south of the mouth of the Mississippi River, or
about 100 miles southeast of New Orleans.
</TEXT>
