<HEAD>Tennessee Team Wins College Bridge Tourney</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RENO, Nev. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The University of Tennessee has captured the
North American Collegiate Bridge championship, topping Harvard
University by a score of 106-54.
   Sunday's victory advances the four-man Tennessee team to the
World Junior Championship in Nottingham, England, this fall.
   The University of Tennessee team, made up of Jim Baker, David
Williams, Michael White II and Michael Cappelletti Jr., was one of
six regional collegiate champions that competed at Bally's Reno.
   The other entrants were the University of Illinois, Rice
University, California Institute of Technology and Rensselaer
Polytechnic Institute.
   The weekend competition was held during the North American Bridge
Championships, which began March 10 and were expected to conclude
early Tuesday with the crowning of a national champion from some
6,000 original entrants.
