<FIRST>r a PM-People-O'ConnorSurgery     03-20 0188</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-People-O'Connor Surgery,0192</SECOND>
<UNK>Actor To Have Gall Bladder Surgery While Recovering From Heart Bypass</UNK>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actor Carroll O'Connor, recovering from heart
bypass surgery at Atlanta's Emory University Hospital, developed an
unrelated gall bladder problem and was scheduled for more surgery
today, the hospital said.
   Doctors discovered Saturday that the 64-year-old O'Connor was
suffering from an inflamed gall bladder, hospital spokeswoman Judy
Smith said today.
   ``Studies performed during the weekend revealed a non-functioning
gall bladder,'' she said. When the problem continued, doctors
decided it should be removed.
   The surgery was scheduled for this afternoon.
   O'Connor, best known as Archie Bunker in television's ``All in
the Family,'' was filming his current series, ``In the Heat of the
Night,'' in nearby Covington, Ga., when he was hospitalized for
heart problems March 10. The bypass was performed March 11, and
O'Connor had been scheduled for release from the hospital this week.
   Ms. Smith said doctors do not believe the gall bladder problem is
related to the heart bypass.
   In fact, she said, ``having had his coronary obstructions
corrected, Mr. O'Connor will be able to more safely tolerate this
surgery.''
