<HEAD>Five Killed In Civil War Fighting</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Leads with 7 grafs to update casualties, details on fighting.
Picks up 6th graf pvs ``The clashes pitted...'' </HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Christian and Moslem forces battled today
with heavy artillery and tanks in the capital and the surrounding
hills. Police said five people were killed and 15 wounded.
   The casualties increased the toll to 54 people killed and 179
wounded on the 13th day of the latest round of fighting in Lebanon's
14-year-old civil war.
   Also today, Israeli warplanes bombed what Israel said were Bekaa
Valley bases of the pro-Syrian Popular Front for the Liberation of
Palestine-General Command, a faction of the Palestine Liberation
Organization. Police said six fighter bombers carried out the raid
on the town of Bar Elias, killing six people and wounding nine.
   The Israeli attack came amid continuing artillery clashes between
Christian and Moslem gunners who pounded residential districts on
both sides of Beirut's dividing Green Line.
   A police spokesman said five people, including an army officer,
were killed and 15 wounded, four of them soldiers.
   The spokesman, who cannot be identified under standing
regulations, said the Christian and Moslem forces battled with tanks
and heavy artillery around Souk el-Gharb, an army garrison town 15
miles southeast of the capital.
   Shells fell on at least 10 residential neighborhoods on both
sides of the frontline in Souk el-Gharb, the spokesman said. He said
shells also hit the Christian ports of Beirut and Jounieh and the
airport highway in Moslem west Beirut. The airport has been closed
since March 11.
   The clashes pitted predominantly Christian units of army
commander Gen. Michel Aoun against Syrian-backed fighters of Druse
warlord Walid Jumblatt's Progressive Socialist Party militia.
   Aoun also leads a Christian Cabinet that rivals a Moslem Cabinet
in this divided nation.
   Mediation efforts to broker a settlement in the new flare-up of
fighting have been deadlocked.
</TEXT>
