<HEAD>Grenade Kills 3 Children, Injures 3 Others</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MONROVIA, Liberia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Children playing near a church found a
grenade and it exploded when they dropped it, killing three of them
and injuring three others, a witness and officials said Monday.
   The children had been playing marbles Sunday outside the suburban
church when one of them found the ordnance and handed it to a
friend. The grenade exploded when the friend dropped it, a witness
said.
   The three injured youths were seriously hurt.
   Police and military officials said they were investigating the
incident. No other details were released.
</TEXT>
