<HEAD>U.S. Settles with Indian Fisherman's Family</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANAMA, Bahrain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. government agreed to pay $18,000
to the family of an Indian fisherman killed in a 1987 shooting
incident involving an American warship in the gulf, U.S. diplomatic
sources said Monday.
   The sources said on condition of anonytmity that the settlement
was reached with relatives of Jagdish Baghwan, 22, of Gujarat, India.
   Baghwan was a crew member on a fishing craft that was fired on by
the missile frigate USS Carr off the United Arab Emirates on Nov. 1,
