attacks by Iranian armed speedboats in the southern Gulf, where the
nighttime incident occurred.
   The diplomatic sources said the settlement, equivalent to about
$18,000, was the maximum allowed under Emirates law in such cases.
The Indian government had asked for a $25,000 compensation,
according to the U.A.E. newspaper Khaleej Times.
