<HEAD>NHTSA Chief Named</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush said Monday he will nominate
retired Army Gen. Jerry Ralph Curry to be head of the National
Highway Traffic Safety Administration.
   If confirmed, he would succeed Diane K. Stead.
   Before retiring from the Army, Curry was deputy commanding
general of V Corps in Frankfurt, West Germany. Previously, he was
commanding general of the Army Test and Evaluation Command in
Aberdeen Proving Ground, Md., and commanding general of the Army
Military District of Washington, D.C.
