<HEAD>Passenger Bus Careens Into Ditch, Killing 15</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A passenger bus careened off a roadway and
plunged into a 100-foot-deep gulley Monday, killing at least 15
people and injuring 35 others, news reports said.
   The Excelsior news service said the accident on the
Naucalpan-Toluca state highway outside Mexico City occurred about
7:20 a.m. (8:30 a.m. EST). No other vehicles were involved.
   The news service quoted rescue officials as saying 15 were
confirmed dead. Nacaulpan Red Cross dispatcher Jesus Rangel said
many of the 35 wounded suffered serious injuries and were taken to
nearby hospitals.
   Rescue attempts were hampered by the depth of the gulley and
faulty rescue equipment, the news service said.
   More than 30 Red Cross, fire department and federal highway
police units at midday were still pulling bodies and the injured out
of the wreckage, Excelsior said.
   Surviving passengers reportedly told authorities the bus was
traveling very fast when the vehicle left the roadway and plummeted
into the ditch.
   Among those reported killed was the driver. His name was not
immediately available.
   Nacaulpan is in the state of Mexico just north of Mexico City.
