<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   American Express Co. is offering travel bargains
and launching a magazine for college students who carry the American
Express card, the company said.
   Fulltime college students can get an American Express card
without meeting any minimum income requirement and without a parent
as co-signer, provided they do not have a bad credit record. The
annual fee is $55, the same as for regular cardholders, and payment
in full is due every month.
   Under the program, cardholders who are fulltime students at a
four-year college will get two vouchers for round trips at $99 each
between any two domestic destinations served by Northwest Airlines
in the 48 contiguous states.
   In addition, they will get vouchers for reduced rates on
Northwest to specific destinations and bonus mileage toward
Northwest's free travel program.
   American Express also plans to publish a quarterly lifestyle
magazine, American Express Connections, that will be sent to its
college student cardholders. Included in the magazine will be tips
on travel and money management.
