<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Labor Department reported wholesale prices
rose 1.0 percent in February, equalling January's surprising rise
and projecting an annual wholesale inflation rate of 12.6 percent.
   The report on inflation belted the stock and bond markets Friday,
with the Dow Jones industrial average plunging nearly 50 points on
fears of spiraling prices, crushingly high interest rates and a
possible recession.
   Economists said if the Federal Reserve boosts interest rates too
high in its effort to cool off the economy and dampen inflation, it
could accidentally cut short the record 6{-year-old economic
expansion.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The sharp stock market sell-off sparked by
renewed inflation fears triggered futures trading limits aimed at
preventing another market crash.
   The price limits on stock-index futures trading on the Chicago
Mercantile Exchange were used Friday for the first time since being
imposed last year by major financial markets.
   Last October, the Securities and Exchange Commission and the
Commodity Futures Trading Commission approved the so-called
``circuit-breaker'' measures designed to calm jittery, volatile
markets and prevent a repeat of the Black Monday crash of Oct. 19,
1987.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
