<FIRST>u f AM-EconomicReportCard-List 1stLd-Writethru   03-20 0339</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Economic Report Card-List, 1st Ld-Writethru,0212</SECOND>
<HEAD>For Release at 6:30 p.m. EST</HEAD>
<HEAD>Research Group's State-by-State Economic Report Card</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: CORRECTS safety in graf 4, bgng ``This includes''</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Economic Report Card</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the state-by-state economic report card
issued Monday by the Corporation for Enterprise Development, a
private, non-profit reserach group.
   The grades are in four areas:
   _Economic performance, shown here as PER.
   This includes such factors as employment, earnings, job quality,
poverty, income distribution, crime, and environmental safety and
health.
   _Business vitality, shown here as VIT.
   This refers to the competitiveness of existing businesses,
industrial diversity, and the ability to generate new jobs in new
businesses.
   _Economic capacity, shown here as CAP.
   This covers human, technological, physical and financial
resources.
   _Policy strength, shown here as POL.
   This measures policies on taxes, education, infrastructure,
business support, and development, and toward disadvantaged
communities and individuals.
</TEXT>
